The paper presents a neural network module designed for modeling interactions among elements in a set, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of attention mechanisms and the focus on permutation invariance suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
